consider something like this:

void setDimmObject(...) {
  getDimmInventoryItem(..., [...](...) {
    setDimmData(...);
  });
}

void getDimmObject(...) {
  getDimmInventoryItem(..., [...](...) {
    getDimmData(...);
  });
}

set/get are still separated and there is getDimmInventoryItem which only performs get (you can pass callback which does something else like set, but that's something common in bmcweb also there doesn't seem to be other way around it when we are dealing with async_calls)
